   "source": [
    "import os\n",
    "from pathlib import Path\n",
    "\n",
    "candidate_paths = [Path(\"/content/preference_pairs.jsonl\"), Path(\"/content/training_data/preference_pairs.jsonl\")]\n",
    "found = next((p for p in candidate_paths if p.exists()), None)\n",
    "if found:\n",
    "    print(f\"Found preference pairs at {found}. You are ready to run the training cells.\")\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    print(\"Preference pairs not found. Upload training_data/preference_pairs.jsonl to /content or /content/training_data/.\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "fxLbRJIz-CZg"
   },
   "source": [
    "# Tenacious-Bench — Path B SimPO Training\n",
    "\n",
    "**What this notebook does:**\n",
    "- Loads a text-only Qwen 2.5 0.5B Instruct backbone with 16-bit LoRA via Unsloth\n",
    "- Trains a Tenacious-specific judge/critic using SimPO (reference-free preference optimization)\n",
    "- Evaluates preference-margin accuracy on the eval split\n",
    "- Pushes the LoRA adapter to HuggingFace\n",
    "\n",
    "**Why not Qwen3.5-0.8B here:** the current Qwen3.5-0.8B HF/Unsloth release is a vision-language model. TRL CPO currently calls the processor positionally, which routes text prompts through the image loader and fails with `Incorrect image source`. It also falls back to float32 on T4. This notebook uses the text-only Qwen2.5 0.5B operational fallback so the Path B run can finish on free Colab.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Before running:**\n",
    "1. Upload `training_data/preference_pairs.jsonl` from your local repo using the Colab file panel (folder icon on the left)\n",
    "2. Add your HuggingFace write token to Colab Secrets (key icon on the left) as `HF_TOKEN`\n",
    "3. Runtime → Change runtime type → T4 GPU\n",
    "\n",
    "**Seed used:** 3407\n",
    "\n",
    "**Expected artifacts:** `training_artifacts/training_run.log`, `training_artifacts/trainer_log_history.jsonl`, `training_artifacts/loss_curve.png`, and `training_artifacts/eval_preference_margin.json`"
   ]
  },
