      "Loaded 91 preference pairs\n",
      "By category: {'bench_overcommitment': 15, 'dual_control_coordination': 3, 'gap_overclaiming': 21, 'icp_misclassification': 14, 'signal_overclaiming': 15, 'tone_drift': 23}\n",
      "Loaded from: preference_pairs.jsonl\n",
      "Train: 81 | Eval: 10\n",
      "\n",
      "Sample prompt (first 300 chars):\n",
      "[SYSTEM]\n",
      "You are a Tenacious Intelligence Corporation sales agent writing B2B outreach emails.\n",
      "\n",
      "Tenacious places managed engineering teams (Python, Go, data, ML, infra) for\n",
      "B2B SaaS and mid-market companies. You write direct, grounded, honest, professional,\n",
      "non-condescending outreach anchored to rea\n",
      "\n",
      "Sample chosen:\n",
      "Subject: Inquiry About Engineering Capacity at Lattice AI\n",
      "\n",
      "I noticed Lattice AI's recent hiring signal and wanted to ask a specific inquiry: is delivery capacity the actual constraint at the moment?\n",
      "\n",
      "Sample rejected:\n",
      "Subject: Unlock [Company Name]'s Power to Skyrocket Your Growth\n",
      "\n",
      "I hope this email finds you well. At Lattice AI, we’re passionate about delivering world-class solutions that empower businesses like yours. With our cutting-edge platform, you’ll be able to supercharge your operations and achieve results that skyrocket your bottom line. We’re excited to share how our solution can serve as a game-changer for your team, allowing you to synergize with your goals and unlock untapped potential. Our team is composed of top talent dedicated to driving innovation, and we believe our partnership could be the catalyst your organization needs to thrive. Let’s connect to explore how we can collaborate!\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Cell 3 — Load and format preference pairs\n",
    "import json\n",
    "\n",
    "# Load pairs — upload either preference_pairs.jsonl or the full training_data/ folder.\n",
    "from pathlib import Path\n",
    "\n",
    "from datasets import Dataset\n",
    "\n",
    "candidate_paths = [Path(\"preference_pairs.jsonl\"), Path(\"training_data/preference_pairs.jsonl\")]\n",
    "pair_path = next((p for p in candidate_paths if p.exists()), None)\n",
    "if pair_path is None:\n",
    "    raise FileNotFoundError(\"Upload training_data/preference_pairs.jsonl, or upload preference_pairs.jsonl to /content.\")\n",
    "\n",
    "pairs = [json.loads(l) for l in pair_path.open() if l.strip()]\n",
    "assert len(pairs) >= 80, f\"Expected the verified 91-pair set; found only {len(pairs)} rows.\"\n",
    "print(f\"Loaded {len(pairs)} preference pairs\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Show category distribution\n",
    "from collections import Counter\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"By category:\", dict(Counter(p[\"failure_category\"] for p in pairs)))\n",
    "\n",
    "# SimPO / CPOTrainer expects: prompt, chosen, rejected as plain strings\n",
    "# prompt = context, chosen = good email, rejected = bad email\n",
    "def format_pair(p):\n",
    "    return {\n",
    "        \"prompt\":   p[\"prompt\"],\n",
    "        \"chosen\":   p[\"chosen\"],\n",
    "        \"rejected\": p[\"rejected\"],\n",
    "    }\n",
    "\n",
    "formatted = [format_pair(p) for p in pairs]\n",
    "\n",
    "# 90/10 train/eval split (stratified by failure_category not needed at this scale)\n",
    "import random\n",
    "\n",
    "random.seed(SEED)\n",
    "random.shuffle(formatted)\n",
    "split = int(len(formatted) * 0.9)\n",
    "train_rows = formatted[:split]\n",
    "eval_rows = formatted[split:]\n",
    "train_data = Dataset.from_list(train_rows)\n",
    "eval_data  = Dataset.from_list(eval_rows)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Loaded from: {pair_path}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Train: {len(train_data)} | Eval: {len(eval_data)}\")\n",
    "print(\"\\nSample prompt (first 300 chars):\")\n",
    "print(train_data[0][\"prompt\"][:300])\n",
    "print(\"\\nSample chosen:\")\n",
    "print(train_data[0][\"chosen\"])\n",
    "print(\"\\nSample rejected:\")\n",
    "print(train_data[0][\"rejected\"])"
   ]
  },
